name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: As a former judge myself, this is not about politics – it's what judges do to ensure trust and confidence in our justice system.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Justice Thomas must recuse himself from cases pertaining to the events of January 6th. It is unethical for him to take part in any matter that could relate to texts or information in which his wife was involved.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Thank you to the @JoeBiden Administration for protecting and expanding the ACA.  Many happy returns #ACA!

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: My Democratic Attorneys General (@DAGA) colleagues and I have successfully defended the #ACA all the way to @SCOTUS. We will continue to defend access to safe, accessible medical care for all, including those with pre-existing conditions.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Happy Birthday #ACA! Nearly half a million Oregonians rely on the #AffordableCareAct for critical medical coverage – which is why I have defended the #ACA from relentless attacks since President Obama signed it into law 12 years ago this week.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: I’m thrilled to celebrate #womenshistorymonth2022  with the historic nomination of Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson to #SCOTUS. Now let's make sure Judge Jackson is quickly confirmed by the Senate. This is how history is made!

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Equal Pay Day is an appalling reminder that we still have a long way to go to achieve true gender parity. Today marks how far into the new year a woman must work to make the same as a man made the previous year, and it only gets worse for women of color. We must do better.
